1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:10,125
♪

2
00:00:10,208 --> 00:00:11,166
[TAKUYA]
Taiyo.

3
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:13,916
[YUKI]
Father?!

4
00:00:17,958 --> 00:00:22,083
No! Stop it!

5
00:00:22,166 --> 00:00:24,875
♪

6
00:00:30,666 --> 00:00:31,750
[grunts]

7
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:39,625
You made it, bodies intact.

8
00:00:39,708 --> 00:00:40,833
[TAKUYA grunts]

9
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:42,125
You bastard.

10
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:44,875
♪

11
00:00:44,958 --> 00:00:45,916
[BOTH gasp]

12
00:02:20,458 --> 00:02:22,833
[panting]

13
00:02:26,541 --> 00:02:28,125
[YUKI groaning]

14
00:02:28,208 --> 00:02:29,375
[weakly]
Akira.

15
00:02:29,458 --> 00:02:30,625
[panting]

16
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:33,583
[groaning]
The strength... of your will

17
00:02:33,666 --> 00:02:36,708
is everything in this place,
Miss Yuki.

18
00:02:36,791 --> 00:02:38,916
Don't give up, okay?

19
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,458
[panting]

20
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,500
[TAIYO] You know very well
you can't escape, Daichi.

21
00:02:56,333 --> 00:02:58,041
There's no time.

22
00:02:58,125 --> 00:03:00,625
I've come because the Lost
must be completed.

23
00:03:00,708 --> 00:03:03,708
Are you kidding me?
Monster.

24
00:03:03,791 --> 00:03:06,916
Thousands of lives
have been sacrificed.

25
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,416
-Isn't that enough?
-No, I don't think so.

26
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:11,625
Not nearly enough.

27
00:03:11,708 --> 00:03:13,375
[YUKI panting]

28
00:03:13,458 --> 00:03:16,333
[TAIYO]
Daichi, get out here.

29
00:03:17,875 --> 00:03:21,250
You really want to stop
the Lost that badly, do you?

30
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:24,250
We're trying to save
our world, remember?

31
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:26,416
Don't be selfish.

32
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:28,833
Think for a moment
of all our comrades out there

33
00:03:28,916 --> 00:03:30,541
who are suffering.

34
00:03:30,625 --> 00:03:32,791
What's giving you doubts
about this now?

35
00:03:32,875 --> 00:03:34,958
[panting]

36
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:36,958
That thing?

37
00:03:37,958 --> 00:03:39,833
The result of a dumb mistake?

38
00:03:40,916 --> 00:03:42,458
Easy fix.

39
00:03:42,541 --> 00:03:44,458
I'll erase it,
along with your doubt.

40
00:03:45,708 --> 00:03:46,583
[TAKUYA grunts]

41
00:03:46,666 --> 00:03:48,208
[grunting]

42
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:50,125
[YUKI gasps]

43
00:03:51,625 --> 00:03:52,875
How did you do that?

44
00:03:54,583 --> 00:03:56,166
[gasps]

45
00:03:56,250 --> 00:03:59,083
No, the medicine
should still be working.

46
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:10,416
[gasps]

47
00:04:11,958 --> 00:04:13,541
Taiyo?

48
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:15,750
[gasps]
You see? It's true.

49
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,833
I knew I would
remember you perfectly.

50
00:04:19,166 --> 00:04:21,791
So through continual
mutual confirmation,

51
00:04:21,875 --> 00:04:23,833
you've maintained an existence.

52
00:04:23,916 --> 00:04:25,791
[scoffs]

53
00:04:25,875 --> 00:04:27,791
How very heroic.

54
00:04:27,875 --> 00:04:29,916
However, compared to what
I've had to shoulder,

55
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,333
my old friend,
it's almost embarrassingly weak.

56
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:36,708
[gasps]

57
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:43,916
I'm here now, Dad.

58
00:04:48,208 --> 00:04:50,000
[sobbing quietly]

59
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:52,708
Please, sir.

60
00:04:52,791 --> 00:04:55,000
Why did you ask Yuki
to come to Lost?

61
00:04:55,083 --> 00:04:56,625
Tell us.

62
00:04:56,708 --> 00:04:57,875
What's the point?

63
00:04:57,958 --> 00:05:00,250
She's suffering here,
can't you see?

64
00:05:01,625 --> 00:05:03,291
♪

65
00:05:10,875 --> 00:05:12,083
[BOTH gasp]

66
00:05:15,416 --> 00:05:16,541
[inaudible]

67
00:05:26,083 --> 00:05:27,833
[gasps]

68
00:05:27,916 --> 00:05:28,875
What does that mean?

69
00:05:29,916 --> 00:05:32,125
That she can choose for herself?

70
00:05:32,208 --> 00:05:34,083
[groans softly]

71
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:36,291
♪

72
00:05:43,791 --> 00:05:45,333
[YUKI]
But what does that mean?

73
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:52,875
[YUKI sobs quietly]

74
00:06:09,166 --> 00:06:10,250
[chuckles]

75
00:06:14,125 --> 00:06:14,958
[gasps]

76
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,208
[MIFUYU] Hey, Souma,
did you grab your lunch box?

77
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:21,375
Yeah, I've got it.

78
00:06:21,458 --> 00:06:23,125
[MIFUYU]
Yuki.

79
00:06:23,208 --> 00:06:25,250
How long do you plan
on messing with your hair?

80
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:27,958
You're gonna be late.

81
00:06:28,041 --> 00:06:29,583
[YUKI]
Almost done.

82
00:06:31,125 --> 00:06:32,333
[chuckles]

83
00:06:32,416 --> 00:06:34,166
I guess she's finally
reached that age.

84
00:06:37,541 --> 00:06:38,625
I'm off.

85
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:41,708
[MIFUYU] On their way.
Thanks, Akira.

86
00:06:41,791 --> 00:06:43,208
Take care of my babies, okay?

87
00:06:43,291 --> 00:06:44,500
It's my pleasure, ma'am.

88
00:06:46,375 --> 00:06:48,916
[SOUMA]
Man, tests are the worst.

89
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,833
Well, that attitude
isn't gonna help.

90
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:54,125
If you paid attention in class,
you should be just fine.

91
00:06:54,208 --> 00:06:56,958
Miss Yuki always seems
to do well in class.

92
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:58,541
What are you trying
to say, you jerk,

93
00:06:58,625 --> 00:07:00,125
that I'm stupid
compared to her?

94
00:07:00,208 --> 00:07:02,666
[AKIRA] Of course that's not
what I'm saying.

95
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:05,333
[SOUMA] I just haven't gotten
serious yet, that's all.

96
00:07:05,416 --> 00:07:07,416
[YUKI]
Well, then, get serious.

97
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,125
[SOUMA scoffs]
Maybe someday.

98
00:07:09,208 --> 00:07:12,208
Any moment now, the car
carrying the president

99
00:07:12,291 --> 00:07:13,875
of Lacuna Chemical
will drive by.

100
00:07:14,958 --> 00:07:16,833
Here they are.
If you're just joining us,

101
00:07:16,916 --> 00:07:19,500
the president and vice president
of Lacuna Chemical

102
00:07:19,583 --> 00:07:21,166
have been charged
with using children

103
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:24,666
from an orphanage
for cruel human experimentation.

104
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:27,791
Unfortunately, we aren't able
to see much since they're...

105
00:07:27,875 --> 00:07:29,750
You should be very proud.
Great work.

106
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,333
[REPORTER] ...are simply
stunning and unlike...

107
00:07:31,416 --> 00:07:32,708
[TAKUYA]
Thank you, sir.

108
00:07:32,791 --> 00:07:34,083
[REPORTER] ...the children
were allegedly...

109
00:07:34,166 --> 00:07:36,666
Poor kids had
nowhere else to go.

110
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:39,416
-It's terrible.
-[REPORTER] The video...

111
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:42,375
[SOUMA] I told you I didn't want
any peas, Mom.

112
00:07:42,458 --> 00:07:43,958
[MIFUYU]
Try not to be so picky.

113
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:46,958
[SOUMA]
What about Dad? That's not fair.

114
00:07:47,041 --> 00:07:49,416
-[knock on door]
-[YOSHIAKI] Come in.

115
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:51,750
[MAN]
It's almost time.

116
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:53,833
[YOSHIAKI]
Right, yeah.

117
00:07:55,375 --> 00:07:56,583
[exhales]

118
00:07:56,666 --> 00:07:59,250
[MAN]
What's wrong? Are you nervous?

119
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,125
[gasps]

120
00:08:01,208 --> 00:08:02,625
[TSUBASA]
I mean, aren't you a magician?

121
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:05,500
Gotta keep your cool
at all times.

122
00:08:05,583 --> 00:08:08,916
[YOSHIAKI gasps]
Tsubasa! Where have you been?

123
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:12,500
[HOMURA] Now, thanks
to every single one of you,

124
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:15,416
we're finally able
to stand up here, all together.

125
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:17,541
[NAMI]
It's been crazy getting here,

126
00:08:17,625 --> 00:08:19,916
but we got through it
because of each other.

127
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,708
And now that
we've come this far,

128
00:08:21,791 --> 00:08:24,208
I can't imagine anything
holding us back.

129
00:08:24,291 --> 00:08:26,500
[HARUKA] We're gonna continue
pushing forward at top speed

130
00:08:26,583 --> 00:08:28,125
with all we've got.

131
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:31,333
So, try to keep up, okay?
We don't wanna leave you behind.

132
00:08:31,416 --> 00:08:32,625
[kisses]

133
00:08:32,708 --> 00:08:34,875
[RENA] Salty Haruka blew
an actual kiss?

134
00:08:34,958 --> 00:08:36,208
What's even happening?

135
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:39,833
I've decided to
challenge myself this year.

136
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:42,041
And how about you, Rena?

137
00:08:42,125 --> 00:08:43,333
I don't know.

138
00:08:43,416 --> 00:08:46,333
Oh! It'd be cool
not to be known as clumsy.

139
00:08:46,416 --> 00:08:48,291
I hope you'll stay
just the way you are.

140
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:51,708
Yeah? Then Yua gets to keep
being the devious one.

141
00:08:51,791 --> 00:08:54,166
-Hey, now, watch it.
-[GIRLS giggling]

142
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:56,833
Look, I know
that's what everyone says,

143
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:58,750
though there are times
when even I wake up

144
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:01,000
with a wet pillow
in the morning.

145
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:03,666
But during good times and bad,

146
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:05,666
you were here for us.

147
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:06,958
Because of all of you,

148
00:09:07,041 --> 00:09:09,125
I felt like as long as
we didn't give up,

149
00:09:09,208 --> 00:09:11,000
everything would be okay.

150
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:13,291
Thank you so much,
from our hearts!

151
00:09:13,375 --> 00:09:14,541
[AUDIENCE cheering]

152
00:09:14,625 --> 00:09:17,041
Yes, Yua!

153
00:09:17,125 --> 00:09:18,375
[cries]

154
00:09:20,250 --> 00:09:22,083
♪

155
00:09:27,041 --> 00:09:28,875
[CHIEF] I want to
congratulate you once again

156
00:09:28,958 --> 00:09:30,708
on the
police commissioner award.

157
00:09:30,791 --> 00:09:32,375
Excellent work.

158
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:34,875
[NEGISHI]
Well, it's thanks to all of you.

159
00:09:34,958 --> 00:09:38,625
[RYOKO] Congratulations, Dad,
er, Officer Negishi.

160
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:41,833
[YUJI] I can't believe
you took down Lacuna. Unreal.

161
00:09:41,916 --> 00:09:44,125
[KEIGO] I know you chased
that case for a long time.

162
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:46,000
How about a drink?

163
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:48,125
[NEGISHI] There are still crimes
being committed.

164
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:50,541
It's about to get busier
from here on out.

165
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:51,791
[RYOKO, YUJI and KEIGO]
Yes sir.

166
00:09:53,208 --> 00:09:54,708
Hey, I'm home.

167
00:09:54,791 --> 00:09:57,125
Huh? What?

168
00:09:59,416 --> 00:10:03,041
[ALL singing]
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

169
00:10:03,125 --> 00:10:07,000
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

170
00:10:07,083 --> 00:10:10,958
♪ Happy birthday, dear Yuki ♪

171
00:10:27,958 --> 00:10:29,625
[YUKI sobbing quietly]

172
00:10:43,458 --> 00:10:44,958
[YUKI]
I won't...

173
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:47,000
I won't do it.

174
00:10:47,083 --> 00:10:48,875
I can't choose.

175
00:10:52,208 --> 00:10:53,875
Of course.

176
00:10:53,958 --> 00:10:57,666
I think it would've been better
if the Lost had never happened.

177
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:59,500
But it happened,

178
00:10:59,583 --> 00:11:02,541
and most of us had to continue
to live in this world.

179
00:11:04,708 --> 00:11:07,208
These last three years,

180
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:09,833
people have desperately
pressed on.

181
00:11:11,166 --> 00:11:14,500
Even though their loved ones
suddenly disappeared,

182
00:11:14,583 --> 00:11:17,541
they never gave up on life.

183
00:11:17,625 --> 00:11:21,250
They didn't know how
or why things went wrong,

184
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:24,500
but they chose
to keep moving forward.

185
00:11:24,583 --> 00:11:27,666
And what about those
who were born after the Lost?

186
00:11:29,625 --> 00:11:32,041
If I choose one universe,

187
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:34,666
it means I reject
the existence of the other.

188
00:11:36,958 --> 00:11:38,750
I can't do something like that.

189
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:40,250
I can't, Dad.

190
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:42,500
♪

191
00:11:42,583 --> 00:11:43,625
[sniffles]

192
00:11:47,125 --> 00:11:51,916
The truth is, so many things
have happened to lead us here.

193
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:55,416
They've been difficult
and painful,

194
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,041
but it's about more than that.

195
00:11:58,333 --> 00:12:02,166
We pulled together
and depended on each other.

196
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:05,541
We discovered
how strong we were.

197
00:12:11,166 --> 00:12:14,166
[TAKUYA] No matter what happens,
that won't change.

198
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:16,333
We'll fight and grow.

199
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:19,916
The past is done,
but the future...

200
00:12:21,708 --> 00:12:25,125
that's still there
waiting for us.

201
00:12:25,208 --> 00:12:27,250
♪

202
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:32,416
[YUKI]
The Lost happened.

203
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:37,166
I can't and won't forget.

204
00:12:39,791 --> 00:12:41,416
I have to stay here.

205
00:12:43,916 --> 00:12:47,666
So, Dad, thanks so much.

206
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:50,666
But you know, I'm not a quitter.

207
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:53,916
That's not who you
raised me to be.

208
00:12:59,375 --> 00:13:00,458
[BOTH gasp]

209
00:13:00,541 --> 00:13:03,666
[YUKI screaming]

210
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:06,416
♪

211
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:09,708
[GEEK grunts]

212
00:13:09,791 --> 00:13:12,666
-Okay, what was that?
-I'm not quite sure.

213
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:16,083
There's a huge burst of
gravitational waves near Lost.

214
00:13:16,166 --> 00:13:17,416
[KIKYO]
What's happening inside?

215
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:19,458
[gasps]
Takuya!

216
00:13:22,666 --> 00:13:23,875
[JACK]
It's coming from Lost.

217
00:13:23,958 --> 00:13:26,375
[SUMIRE] But we can't
get any closer.

218
00:13:26,458 --> 00:13:27,416
[JACK]
Shit!

219
00:13:31,458 --> 00:13:32,500
[TAIYO]
Daichi.

220
00:13:34,875 --> 00:13:37,250
Enough of your boastful drivel.

221
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:42,250
I will simply
eliminate you entirely,

222
00:13:42,333 --> 00:13:45,041
and then I'll finally
complete the Lost.

223
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:48,375
I will succeed.

224
00:13:48,458 --> 00:13:51,583
Millions of people's
futures depend upon it.

225
00:13:52,625 --> 00:13:55,208
Stop this, now!

226
00:13:55,291 --> 00:13:56,250
[grunts]

227
00:13:57,583 --> 00:13:58,750
[roars]

228
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:00,250
[gasps]

229
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:02,416
♪

230
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:05,458
[TAIYO growls]

231
00:14:06,458 --> 00:14:08,000
[groans sharply]

232
00:14:08,083 --> 00:14:09,375
Yuki.

233
00:14:09,458 --> 00:14:11,041
[TAIYO roars]

234
00:14:11,125 --> 00:14:12,500
[TAIYO]
This is the end.

235
00:14:17,625 --> 00:14:18,666
[grunts]

236
00:14:20,625 --> 00:14:21,500
[gasps]

237
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:33,250
[bullet thumps]

238
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:34,416
[gasps]

239
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:35,416
[bullet thumps]

240
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:38,833
[groans]

241
00:14:48,166 --> 00:14:49,458
[TAIYO]
Did you actually believe

242
00:14:49,541 --> 00:14:51,750
I wouldn't be able
to see this coming?

243
00:14:54,291 --> 00:14:56,125
♪

244
00:14:59,916 --> 00:15:00,875
[TAIYO groans sharply]

245
00:15:02,166 --> 00:15:04,166
[grunting]

246
00:15:06,416 --> 00:15:08,166
[TAIYO]
Damn Suzuna.

247
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:10,875
She predicted it
up to this point.

248
00:15:10,958 --> 00:15:13,333
♪

249
00:15:30,958 --> 00:15:34,250
[AKIRA]
Yuki. Yuki.

250
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:35,833
This is your chance.

251
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:41,625
Use that against Taiyo.

252
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:54,375
[YUKI]
Takuya.

253
00:15:55,875 --> 00:15:57,666
[TAIYO grunting]

254
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,333
[roars]

255
00:16:03,041 --> 00:16:05,625
[growling]

256
00:16:07,666 --> 00:16:09,708
[groaning]

257
00:16:11,583 --> 00:16:13,458
♪

258
00:16:16,541 --> 00:16:18,041
[groaning]

259
00:16:20,166 --> 00:16:23,333
[DAICHI] Get on the scooter.
Do it. Now!

260
00:16:27,458 --> 00:16:28,958
[groans]

261
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:34,375
[motor scooter engine starts]

262
00:16:34,458 --> 00:16:35,541
[DAICHI]
Yuki...

263
00:16:37,291 --> 00:16:39,125
you've grown up so much.

264
00:17:08,416 --> 00:17:10,500
[GEEK]
Jack, did you hear?

265
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:11,916
Yeah.

266
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,500
-Huh?
-[gasps]

267
00:17:13,583 --> 00:17:16,000
-[gasps]
-[JACK] That's... It's her.

268
00:17:19,125 --> 00:17:20,375
[car doors open]

269
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:23,500
Hey, wake up. Come on!

270
00:17:23,583 --> 00:17:24,791
Where is he?

271
00:17:24,875 --> 00:17:26,541
Yuki!

272
00:17:26,625 --> 00:17:30,083
Takuya!

273
00:17:32,416 --> 00:17:34,791
♪

274
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:40,166
[YOSHIAKI] I'd hate to make
a tree disappear.

275
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:42,625
I don't think anyone
would appreciate that.

276
00:17:42,708 --> 00:17:45,666
So today I'll focus
on this bottle.

277
00:17:45,750 --> 00:17:49,583
-One, two, three.
-[WOMAN 1] Will it work? Wow.

278
00:17:51,208 --> 00:17:52,166
-[cheering]
-[WOMAN 2] Wow!

279
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,625
Did you see what he did?

280
00:17:53,708 --> 00:17:55,708
Thank you very much.

281
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:57,500
Really appreciate it.

282
00:17:57,583 --> 00:17:59,875
Sure. We can do that.

283
00:17:59,958 --> 00:18:01,958
Investigating your husband's
cheating habits

284
00:18:02,041 --> 00:18:04,791
will run you right around
100,000 yen a day.

285
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:07,083
-Huh? Uh... Hey. W... Hey!
-[cell phone beeps]

286
00:18:07,166 --> 00:18:09,375
I don't wanna chase
cheating husbands.

287
00:18:09,458 --> 00:18:11,083
I wanna do jobs that matter.

288
00:18:11,166 --> 00:18:13,125
[KEIGO]
Beggars can't be choosers.

289
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:15,541
Just go back
to the police force.

290
00:18:15,625 --> 00:18:16,708
[YUJI ]
Believe me, if I could've,

291
00:18:16,791 --> 00:18:18,500
I'd be there already.

292
00:18:18,583 --> 00:18:21,000
[EIJI] In other words,
the problem of Lost

293
00:18:21,083 --> 00:18:23,375
is one that belongs
to everyone on Earth.

294
00:18:23,458 --> 00:18:26,416
Its effects unfortunately
reach all of mankind.

295
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:28,666
So, in response to that,

296
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:31,458
our foundation is creating
a project team.

297
00:18:31,541 --> 00:18:33,833
Recruiting talent,
no matter where from.

298
00:18:33,916 --> 00:18:35,500
If you can help
with this difficult problem,

299
00:18:35,583 --> 00:18:38,041
we ask you to reach out
and join us.

300
00:18:38,125 --> 00:18:40,750
[camera shutters clicking]

301
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,625
[chalk scribbling]

302
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:57,208
[cell phone vibrates]

303
00:18:57,291 --> 00:18:58,208
Huh?

304
00:19:13,958 --> 00:19:16,041
[GEEK] How's Yuki
doing these days?

305
00:19:16,125 --> 00:19:17,583
[EIJI sighs]

306
00:19:17,666 --> 00:19:20,916
She seems to have slowly
acclimated to her daily life.

307
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:24,791
Her complaints are normal.
"Studying is hard," etcetera.

308
00:19:26,375 --> 00:19:29,500
What about the issue
with her memory?

309
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:34,375
Well, she's having trouble
remembering a certain courier,

310
00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:35,750
if you believe that.

311
00:19:36,916 --> 00:19:38,833
[EIJI] She made it out,
but she was exposed

312
00:19:38,916 --> 00:19:40,666
to the surge particles
for too long.

313
00:19:48,041 --> 00:19:49,666
-Hey, Yuki.
-Huh?

314
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:52,791
I'm headed this way, too.

315
00:19:52,875 --> 00:19:54,916
[YUKI]
Oh, cool.

316
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,916
Have you been
keeping up in class?

317
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,083
[YUKI]
Hmm.

318
00:19:58,166 --> 00:20:00,125
I mean, barely, I guess.

319
00:20:00,208 --> 00:20:02,458
Make sure and ask me
if you hit any problems.

320
00:20:02,541 --> 00:20:04,125
I'll lend you my notes.

321
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:06,041
[YUKI]
Great. Thank you.

322
00:20:11,166 --> 00:20:12,083
[gasps softly]

323
00:20:14,125 --> 00:20:15,291
Something wrong?

324
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:18,875
[YUKI]
It's nothing.

325
00:20:20,541 --> 00:20:22,833
[KOUTA]
This is hard.

326
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:26,166
[KAIBARA] That's pretty pathetic
from someone so young.

327
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:27,958
[sighs]

328
00:20:28,041 --> 00:20:30,625
I didn't think it'd be
this much manual labor.

329
00:20:32,125 --> 00:20:32,958
[KAIBARA]
So...

330
00:20:34,875 --> 00:20:36,083
anything new?

331
00:20:36,166 --> 00:20:37,791
Any leads on where he is?

332
00:20:40,083 --> 00:20:41,833
No, sorry.

333
00:20:45,583 --> 00:20:46,875
[YUMIKO]
Thanks for the treat.

334
00:20:48,958 --> 00:20:51,208
I still say we should
brand this tomato, you know.

335
00:20:52,750 --> 00:20:54,583
Let's find a way
to distribute them.

336
00:20:54,666 --> 00:20:55,625
What do you say?

337
00:20:55,708 --> 00:20:57,208
[KAIBARA]
No, no.

338
00:20:57,291 --> 00:21:00,000
I've only ever wanted
to do this as a hobby.

339
00:21:00,083 --> 00:21:02,375
[KOUTA]
Well, I need to head out soon.

340
00:21:02,458 --> 00:21:04,750
[YUMIKO] Don't you still have
work to do here, though?

341
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:07,250
[KOUTA]
What? No. Shut up.

342
00:21:27,083 --> 00:21:28,583
[door opens, closes]

343
00:21:33,416 --> 00:21:35,333
[motor scooter engine revving]

344
00:21:40,041 --> 00:21:41,916
[motor scooter receding]

345
00:21:50,916 --> 00:21:52,416
[wind howling]

346
00:21:57,041 --> 00:22:00,083
♪

